{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5da4b42d-70d6-4101-9ff0-b3e5438da2ab","content":"TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively, so you need `--treenode-filter` (not `--filter`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nThe treenode path format is `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Method`. The `*` wildcards match the assembly and namespace, targeting only the `SmsNotificationTests` class (2 tests: `SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"160ee26f-d83f-40a2-9d23-c43cfab3b965","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively, not VSTest. For MTP-based projects, the filter syntax is different from VSTest's `--filter`.\n\nFor TUnit on MTP, you use `--treenode-filter` to filter tests. To filter by class name, the syntax is:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nThe treenode filter uses a path-like syntax: `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Method`. Using wildcards for assembly and namespace, you can target the class.\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. \n\nThe treenode filter path format is `/AssemblyName/Namespace/ClassName/MethodName`, so I can either use wildcards like `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests` or be more specific with the full path. I should verify whether TUnit actually supports `--filter` or if it's exclusively `--treenode-filter`.\n\nActually, TUnit is built on MTP natively and only uses `--treenode-filter` since `--filter` is a VSTest concept, so the command would be the wildcard version.","outputTokens":506,"requestId":"0BC3:3A1531:3D34EE:4761D8:69F00D5A"},"id":"ff933bb3-9e4a-416d-8a05-22cc61cbb333","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:29:09.790Z","parentId":"a257de36-2ff3-4032-b764-47b257131e30"}
